id: pm-k5e8
title: pm_max_version default-BLOCK should have a per-layer warn-only toggle in settings
description: "loader.ts line 907 has a `// follow-up: pm-4gw6 recommends a future settings toggle to relax this default-BLOCK to warn-only per layer.` comment. Currently pm_max_version exceeded always BLOCKS the extension (allowed: false). This is intentional for safety but creates a footgun for project-layer pinned extensions during a CLI upgrade: the extension silently stops loading until the author publishes a new version. A settings flag like `extensions.policy.pm_max_version_exceeded_mode: 'block'|'warn'` (defaulting to 'block') would let operators running managed installations opt into warn-only during upgrade windows."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:extensions",compat,dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:04:51.632Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-09T18:41:21.810Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- A per-layer setting toggles pm_max_version violation from block to warn\n- Default remains block (backward compatible)\n- Setting documented + validated; covered by tests"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Implemented per-layer pm_max_version_exceeded_mode with block default and warn override.
expected_result: Operators can keep default blocking behavior or opt into warn-only for managed upgrade windows.
actual_result: "Settings, validator, policy normalization, loader behavior, docs, and tests now cover block and warn modes."
